==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[macaque]]'' < Portuguese ''[[macaco]]'' (monkey) < Bantu.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#{{slang}} ''(racial slur)'' A dismissive epithet used by French-speaking colonials in Africa to refer to a person of North African or Subsaharan ethnicity.

